dcterms:description: The SVHN dataset consists of real-world images of house numbers collected from Google Street View. It contains over 600,000 labeled digits and is used for digit recognition tasks.
dcterms:title: SVHN

dcterms:description: CIFAR-10 is a dataset of 60,000 32x32 color images in 10 different classes, with 6,000 images per class. It is commonly used for training machine learning models in image classification tasks.
dcterms:title: CIFAR-10

dcterms:description: Toy Data refers to synthetic datasets created for experimental purposes, typically used to illustrate concepts or test algorithms in a controlled environment.
